Hey all,

HyperNEAT C++ 3.0 is released.  You can get the source code with =
manual here: 
http://www.eecs.ucf.edu/~jgauci/Releases/HyperNEAT_v3_0.zip 
=

The HyperNEAT html reference is updated.  You can access it here:
http://w=
ww.eecs.ucf.edu/~jgauci/Reference/HyperNEAT/

There is a new reference for =
PyHyperNEAT (including the visualizer):
http://www.eecs.ucf.edu/~jgauci/Ref=
erence/PyHyperNEAT/

Here are some of the updates since 2.6:

-PyHyperNEAT:=
 A python wrapper around NEAT and HyperNEAT

-Visualizer: A python substrat=
e visualizer for analyzing the structure of large substrates.  Includes a f=
unction to dump activation levels, receptive fields, and influence maps to =
PDF/SVG/PNG

-Mac OS/X support: The cmake-generated source code now correct=
ly generates an os/x application. OS/X support is now complete for both the=
 GUI and command line versions.

-MPI has been reimplemented and tested wit=
h several cluster experiments.

-Manual included with step-by-step instruct=
ions for adding a new experiment to the system.

-Code reorganization.  Sub=
strate-generation code removed from each experiment in the HyperNEAT librar=
y and added to a common file in the NEAT library.

-Plenty of bug fixes.

P=
lease do not hesitate to post any feedback to this group or via email.

Jas=
on G.
